    <!-- Add STACK exercises if made -->

    <!-- Add static exercises -->

    <exercises>
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>Given that a quantity <m>Y</m> varies as a quantity <m>X</m>:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><p>Find the missing values in Table 9.5.</p></li>
                    <li><p>Find the equation connecting <m>X</m> and <m>Y</m>.</p></li>
                </ol>
                <table>
    
                    <tabular halign="left">
                        <row header="yes" bottom="minor">
                            <cell><m>X</m></cell>
                            <cell>4</cell>
                            <cell>&#8212;</cell>
                            <cell>12</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell><m>Y</m></cell>
                            <cell>2.4</cell>
                            <cell>4.2</cell>
                            <cell>&#8212;</cell>
                        </row>
                    </tabular>
                </table>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>Because <m>Y</m> varies directly as <m>X</m>, write <m>Y = kX</m>. Using <m>X = 4</m> and <m>Y = 2.4</m> gives:</p>
                <p><m>2.4 = k(4) \Rightarrow k = 0.6.</m></p>
                <p>The equation is <m>Y = 0.6X.</m></p>
                <p>For the missing value when <m>Y = 4.2</m>: <m>4.2 = 0.6X \Rightarrow X = 7.</m></p>
                <p>For the missing value when <m>X = 12</m>: <m>Y = 0.6(12) = 7.2.</m></p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p><m>R</m> varies directly as <m>S</m>. If <m>R = 15</m> when <m>S = 5</m>, find:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li><p>the equation connecting <m>R</m> and <m>S</m>;</p></li>
                    <li><p><m>R</m> when <m>S = 12</m>;</p></li>
                    <li><p><m>S</m> when <m>R = 45</m>.</p></li>
                </ol>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>Assume <m>R = kS</m>. Substituting <m>R = 15</m> and <m>S = 5</m> gives:</p>
                <p><m>15 = k(5) \Rightarrow k = 3.</m></p>
                <p>Thus <m>R = 3S.</m></p>
                <p>When <m>S = 12</m>: <m>R = 3(12) = 36.</m></p>
                <p>When <m>R = 45</m>: <m>45 = 3S \Rightarrow S = 15.</m></p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>A quantity <m>V</m> varies directly as a quantity <m>T</m>. If <m>V = 60 \text{ cm}^3</m> when <m>T = 15 \text{ seconds}</m>, find <m>V</m> when <m>T = 40 \text{ seconds}</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>Write <m>V = kT</m>. Using the known values:</p>
                <p><m>60 = k(15) \Rightarrow k = 4.</m></p>
                <p>The relationship is <m>V = 4T.</m></p>
                <p>When <m>T = 40</m>: <m>V = 4(40) = 160 \text{ cm}^3.</m></p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>Given that <m>w</m> varies directly as the square of <m>z</m> and that <m>z = 3</m> when <m>w = 18</m>, find <m>w</m> when <m>z = 5</m>.</p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>Use <m>w = kz^2</m>. Substitute the known values:</p>
                <p><m>18 = k(3^2) = 9k \Rightarrow k = 2.</m></p>
                <p>The formula is <m>w = 2z^2.</m></p>
                <p>When <m>z = 5</m>: <m>w = 2(5^2) = 2(25) = 50.</m></p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
            <statement>
                <p>Given that <m>p</m> is directly proportional to <m>q</m> and the difference in values of <m>p</m> when <m>q = 3</m> and <m>q = 7</m> is <m>20</m>, find the constant of proportionality.</p>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>Since <m>p = kq</m>, the values are <m>p_2 = 7k</m> and <m>p_1 = 3k</m>.</p>
                <p>The difference is <m>7k - 3k = 20 \Rightarrow 4k = 20.</m></p>
                <p>Therefore, <m>k = 5.</m></p>
            </answer>
        </exercise>
    </exercises>

